# Map layout rules

Before adding or moving map chrome:

1. Read `docs/map-ui-mode-matrix.md` and update it if you add a mode or surface.
2. Mount UI in Entry zones (top / map / bottom / ephemeral) — no new fixed overlays in `Map.svelte` except pins and the edit dock. Basemap attribution belongs in `MapAttribution.svelte` on the bottom band, not on the map canvas.
3. Use `.app-layout` CSS vars (`--status-bar-block-height`, `--edit-bar-height`, etc.) — no magic `bottom: 4.25rem`.
4. One flyout at a time: `mapToolsStore` for Map tools; `floatingControlPanelStore` only for contributor propose menu on LocationButton. Editor tools use `editorChromeStore` (search-bar icon + shelf).
5. View controls split: flyout uses `MapViewControls variant="modes"` (Pins + 2D/3D). Desktop map face uses one `camera-controls-card` in `Entry.svelte` (`MapDimensionToggle embedded` + divider + `MapViewControls variant="camera" embedded`), not inside the flyout. Do not mount camera variant on mobile. Mobile 2D/3D only: compact `MapDimensionToggle` in the search chip row (`Search.svelte`).
6. Verify at 320px and 768px: browse, edit mode, map tools open, no bounding-box overlap in the same zone.
